  "prompt": "Who is the old man in the MDH Masala ads and why does he appear in all their ads?",
  "response": "The old man in the MDH Masala ads is **Mahashay Dharampal Gulati**, the owner and CEO of MDH (Mahashian Di Hatti) Spices.\n\nHe appeared in their ads for a very specific reason: **brand identity and trust.**\n\n*   **Building Trust:** In an industry often plagued by concerns about authenticity and quality, having the owner personally endorse the product instilled a sense of trust in consumers. It showed that the company was willing to stand behind its product and that the owner was personally invested in its quality.\n\n*   **Unique Selling Proposition:** His image became synonymous with the brand. In a crowded market, the instantly recognizable old man with the turban and mustache helped MDH stand out. He was a living embodiment of the brand's history and values.\n\n*   **Cost-Effective Marketing:** While it might seem simple, having the owner as the face of the brand was likely a cost-effective marketing strategy, especially in the early days. He was already deeply familiar with the product and the company.\n\nHe was not just a mascot; he was the owner who had built the company from the ground up after migrating to India as a refugee post-partition. His presence conveyed a sense of tradition, heritage, and commitment to quality that resonated with Indian consumers.\n\nMahashay Dharampal Gulati passed away in December 2020.\n",
